WEBVTT

00:00.115 --> 00:01.643
Previously on The O.C.:

00:01.644 --> 00:03.147
What do I have to do to get you to stay?

00:03.148 --> 00:04.259
I think you're doing it.

00:04.260 --> 00:06.645
Julie, you know this engagement is a trial?

00:06.646 --> 00:07.390
What?

00:07.391 --> 00:09.320
Griffin will not move forward unless you are gone.

00:09.321 --> 00:10.939
He's been taking kickbacks from vendors.

00:10.940 --> 00:12.663
Totally and completely untrue.

00:12.664 --> 00:15.382
You give me your word, I'll give you the benefit of the doubt.

00:15.383 --> 00:16.627
What happened?

00:16.782 --> 00:18.112
I know about Volchok.

00:18.111 --> 00:19.676
What has gotten into you?

00:19.773 --> 00:21.059
You're being so lame.

00:21.058 --> 00:22.182
Not as lame as you.

00:22.183 --> 00:24.404
I'm hoping that you both will apply to Berkeley.

00:24.405 --> 00:25.895
That guy from Brown-- he didn't say

00:25.896 --> 00:28.363
they couldn't take more than one student from Harbor.

00:28.364 --> 00:30.292
- Hey, well, this might be the year.
- That's right.

00:36.663 --> 00:38.563
Cohen, come out. I want to see.

00:38.564 --> 00:39.949
All right.

00:43.738 --> 00:45.532
I feel like Pa Kettle.

00:47.237 --> 00:48.969
Not bad. Try this on.

00:48.980 --> 00:50.729
Oh, wow, you got us matching parkas.

00:50.730 --> 00:53.566
Mm-hmm, and matching hats, and matching scarves.

00:53.567 --> 00:56.796
We're going to be the warmest, most coordinated couple at Brown.

00:56.797 --> 00:58.305
Yeah, you think you're jumping the gun a little bit?

00:58.306 --> 01:00.243
We don't get our acceptance letters until tomorrow.

01:00.244 --> 01:03.392
Oh, please, with your dorked-out grades and my NASA-level SATs,

01:03.393 --> 01:04.873
we are so getting in.

01:04.875 --> 01:07.407
It's Brown. Everyone's got good grades and SATs.

01:07.408 --> 01:11.192
It's very possible that neither of us could get in, or that one of us could.

01:11.193 --> 01:13.683
Uh-huh. And which one of us would that be, Cohen?

01:13.684 --> 01:16.063
It's just as likely you'll get in and I won't.

01:16.349 --> 01:17.565
And you really believe that?

01:17.566 --> 01:19.035
Yeah. And then where would you be?

01:19.036 --> 01:22.468
You'd be stuck in Providence with one half of a his-and-hers parka set.

01:22.469 --> 01:24.661
Yeah, like I'd go if you didn't.

01:24.662 --> 01:25.528
What?

01:25.529 --> 01:28.281
Cohen? Duh? I applied to Brown so we could be together.

01:28.282 --> 01:29.617
I'm not going without you.

01:29.618 --> 01:32.573
Summer, Brown is one of the top universities in the world.

01:32.574 --> 01:34.388
People dream about going there.

01:34.389 --> 01:37.486
No, you dream about going there.

01:37.487 --> 01:40.206
I dream about being with the one I love.

01:44.972 --> 01:48.103
Aww, even all padded up, you still look so scrawny.

01:48.104 --> 01:49.338
I'm going to get some water.

01:49.339 --> 01:51.704
I'm sweating so much I'm getting dehydrated.

01:59.082 --> 02:00.571
I thought you were making me dinner.

02:00.572 --> 02:02.144
- And I did.
- Yeah?

02:02.845 --> 02:04.276
You didn't let me eat it.

02:04.277 --> 02:05.901
No one's stopping you.

02:06.184 --> 02:07.410
Really?

02:07.411 --> 02:09.902
- Okay, in that case...
- No.

02:09.904 --> 02:12.650
Oh, no, no.

02:12.651 --> 02:13.864
What?

02:15.805 --> 02:18.251
So with a 90-day escrow,

02:18.734 --> 02:21.674
that means you'll be in town for...

02:21.675 --> 02:24.863
- 90 more days, Einstein.
- Right.

02:25.208 --> 02:26.371
That makes sense.

02:26.372 --> 02:29.518
Until you get accepted to whatever college you applied to.

02:29.519 --> 02:31.061
Yeah.

02:38.314 --> 02:39.884
Okay.

02:39.885 --> 02:41.787
Should I not have mentioned it?

02:41.788 --> 02:44.188
No, no, it's fine. You're right.

02:44.321 --> 02:46.934
Your letter should be arriving, like, tomorrow, right?

02:46.935 --> 02:48.206
Yeah.

02:49.440 --> 02:54.085
I'm sorry, but I found ignoring the future never makes it go away.

02:54.128 --> 02:56.629
Whatever happens, we'll make it work.

02:59.095 --> 03:03.304
Um, we should eat before the burgers get cold, though. I'll grab some water.

03:08.989 --> 03:10.899
- Hi.
- Hi.

03:10.900 --> 03:12.405
You want a water?

03:12.406 --> 03:13.921
Sure.

03:17.340 --> 03:19.466
I was just cooling myself off.

03:20.328 --> 03:25.510
All this time I thought getting into college would make everything so much easier.

03:25.511 --> 03:26.819
Yeah.

03:27.637 --> 03:29.233
Not going to happen.

03:31.096 --> 03:33.280
There's a cold front coming through.

